<br>
Because apparently, according to the game mechanics, everyone in Norrath has learned to identify the uses and purposes and restrictions of items very skillfully. Perhaps the spells used to enchant things leave very easily-identifiable auras. Perhaps Intro to Adventuring 101 (required course for all young folks) includes a complete overview of armor and weapons, along with handy tips on how to ascertain the quality of items.<br>
<br>
In some other games, there are skills that impact one's ability to identify what an item is or what it does, or give varying amounts of information to different people. Not so here, so I see no reason to impose false ignorance on characters.<br>
<br>
The guy who sells fishing bait can identify the subtle differences between various swords well enough to offer varying prices, and apparently so can I.<br>
<br>
