-Caillou Kyrielle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/27/02 2:33:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2204.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: trucking with evil</span><hr size=1> Role-playing does exist independent of the rules in some areas. The reason all items are immediately identifiable to players is to avoid scams. VI decided to sacrifice a bit of reality to create a fairer environment. Player knowledge, not character knowledge. If your character falls prey to a scam, VI wants it to be willing on your part (if you did a story were another 'RL' friend's character stole something from your character for example), not because you didn't know what you were getting into.<br>
<br>
If your character isn't the divine type, he may not know why he can't use that paladin only or shadowknight only sword. It may burn his hands, or leap from his grasp when he tries to use it. The runes on it look innocent enough. All he knows is that Erudite in platemail over there is willing to pay him a lot of money for it.<br>
<br>
The same goes for most RPGs. D&amp;D characters don't know their levels. Nor would they reduce the people of the world to such simple classifications as fighter, mage, rogue, etc... <br>
<br>
There are just things you need to know to make the game more fun. Imagine if you couldn't /con or /who players, and didn't get messages about experience gains. You could group with a friend who's a little too high a level for a week or so before you realize that you’re not improving. Realistic yes, but EQ shouldn't have to hide metagame information from players, just to force players into character. That's the job of the role-player.<br>
